{"id": "1402967547854192752", "channel_id": "1402954293098709023", "type": 0, "author_id": "658320022359375882", "author_name": "vaerre", "author_bot": false, "content": "Sorry, I don't quite understand--why does a hand-drawn, hand-animated, deck-building card game need 120 fps??\nI don't see how increasing the framerate will help the game perform any better than it already is? If anything, it seems like an unnecessary burden to the devs to make happen\nBut feel free to enlighten me <:idk:1356084138280489080>", "timestamp": "2025-08-07T10:52:09.285000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1402954293098709023", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "120 fps mode", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
